&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for people who are relentlessly curious and committed to continuous learning. AI is reshaping every function across our business, and we enable every team member, regardless of role or level, to build fluency in AI tools and concepts. Those who thrive here actively seek out new solutions, experiment thoughtfully, and apply what they learn to drive better, faster, smarter outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As an AI Enablement Engineer, you will be tasked with accelerating the adoption of AI across our R&amp;amp;D organization. This role sits at the intersection of engineering, productivity, innovation, and change management. You will identify, evaluate, and drive the adoption of AI-powered tools, workflows, and engineering practices that improve developer productivity, software quality, operational efficiency, and organizational effectiveness. You will act as a force multiplier for engineering teams, helping transform emerging AI capabilities into measurable business impact. This is a highly cross-functional role requiring a combination of technical depth, experimentation mindset, and strong influence skills. Success will be measured by your ability to discover opportunities, drive adoption, and create lasting improvements in how our teams build, test, secure, and operate software. What Success Looks Like? Within the first year, you will: Establish a clear AI enablement strategy for the R&amp;amp;D organization. Successfully deploy and scale multiple AI-powered workflows across engineering teams. Deliver measurable improvements in developer productivity and engineering efficiency. Build strong AI adoption across the organization through enablement, education, and advocacy. Become the go-to expert for AI innovation and engineering transformation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What Will You Do?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Primary responsibilities include&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI Strategy &amp;amp; Innovation: Continuously evaluate emerging AI technologies, platforms, and industry trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to leverage AI across software development, security, testing, operations, documentation, and knowledge management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Run proof-of-concepts and pilot programs to validate new tools and approaches.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a roadmap for AI adoption across engineering teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developer Productivity &amp;amp; Enable

